<div class="bodyContent">
  <h2 class="navHeading">History of Cacao</h2>

  <div class="historyContent">
    <p class="intro">Cacao has been cultivated for thousands of years, originating in Mesoamerica before spreading across the tropics.</p>

    <div class="historyTimeline">
      <div class="timePeriod">
        <span class="year">1500 BC</span>
        <p>Olmec civilization of Mexico are among the first to cultivate cacao.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timePeriod">
        <span class="year">600 AD</span>
        <p>Maya establish cacao plantations in the Yucatán, using beans as currency.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timePeriod">
        <span class="year">1400s</span>
        <p>Aztec Empire expands cacao trade across Mesoamerica.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timePeriod">
        <span class="year">1500s</span>
        <p>Spanish conquistadors bring cacao to Europe and global demand increases.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timePeriod">
        <span class="year">1800s</span>
        <p>New processing methods turn cacao into mass-produced chocolate.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timePeriod">
        <span class="year">Today</span>
        <p>Over 7.2 million metric tons of cacao produced annually across tropical regions worldwide.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
